# Stability

When making changes, avoid breaking localhost or the UI. Follow these guidelines.

## Prerequisites

- **Git repo**: The pre-commit hook (husky + lint-staged) only runs when the project is a Git repo. If `.git` does not exist, run `git init` so the hook can run `npm run check` on staged files before commits.

## Risky areas (avoid or be extra careful)

- `src/app/layout.tsx` – Prefer globals.css for base styles; avoid arbitrary Tailwind values
- `src/app/globals.css` – Change sparingly
- `tailwind.config.ts` content paths – Keep existing paths; do not broaden or change
- `src/lib/api.ts` – Avoid changing response handling (e.g. res.json vs res.text)
- Prefer theme classes (`bg-stage-dark`) over arbitrary values (`bg-[#0f0f12]`)
- `src/components/DashboardLayoutClient.tsx` – Dashboard layout: sidebar is `hidden lg:flex`, mobile header is `flex lg:hidden`. Do not change these breakpoints or remove `isolate`/`shrink-0`/`w-full` from the layout containers.

## Dev workflow

- Before starting dev server: run `npm run dev:kill` first if another instance might be running
- If localhost stops or UI breaks: suggest `npm run dev:kill` then `rm -rf .next` then `npm run dev`
- Recommend hard refresh (Cmd+Shift+R) after changes

## EMFILE / ulimit

If EMFILE or "too many open files" appears: recommend `ulimit -n 10240` and adding to `~/.zshrc`

## Error page

Keep `error.tsx` and `global-error.tsx` using inline styles, not Tailwind, so they render when styles fail.
